The Vice-Chancellor of the University of Lagos, Prof. Oluwatoyin Ogundipe, has resumed work after his reinstatement. DAILY POST had reported that President Mohammadu Buhari on Wednesday ordered the reinstatement of Ogundipe as the Vice-Chancellor of Lagos State University. Ogundipe who resumed work on Thursday was received by members of staff of UNILAG, including top management personnel, at the Senate Building foyer. He urged the workers to allow peace to reign in the institution. “Let us all be united. It is not about the academic or non-academic staff; it is about UNILAG. “Let us all work together and allow peace in this institution,” he appealed